1
00:00:06,080 --> 00:00:09,449
(Ji Chang Wook)

2
00:00:11,080 --> 00:00:13,949
(Sung Dong Il)

3
00:00:14,820 --> 00:00:17,059
(Choi Soo Young)

4
00:00:17,760 --> 00:00:20,628
(Won Ji An, Nam Tae Hoon, Yang Hee Kyung)

5
00:00:20,629 --> 00:00:23,500
(Kil Hae Yeon, Yu Soon Woong, Jeon Chae Eun, Shin Ju Hwan)

6
00:00:30,800 --> 00:00:34,039
(If You Wish Upon Me)

7
00:00:38,310 --> 00:00:40,310
(Episode 14)

8
00:00:40,750 --> 00:00:41,750
Where are the kids?

9
00:00:42,109 --> 00:00:43,109
What?

10
00:00:44,380 --> 00:00:45,719
Where are the kids?

11
00:00:45,780 --> 00:00:47,289
Hey, what's your problem?

12
00:00:47,689 --> 00:00:48,950
You hit them, didn't you?

13
00:00:49,090 --> 00:00:50,489
What are you talking about?

14
00:00:50,490 --> 00:00:51,820
Did you hit them?

15
00:00:53,189 --> 00:00:54,329
What are you doing?

16
00:01:01,229 --> 00:01:02,299
You little...

17
00:01:10,069 --> 00:01:11,239
Captain.

18
00:01:12,879 --> 00:01:13,879
Gyeo Rye?

19
00:01:16,650 --> 00:01:17,718
Gyeo Rye!

20
00:01:17,719 --> 00:01:20,389
Hey, let me see. What happened to you guys?

21
00:01:20,390 --> 00:01:21,590
Are you all right?

22
00:01:21,950 --> 00:01:24,419
Are you hurt? Did they hit you?

23
00:01:24,420 --> 00:01:26,560
Hit us? Why?

24
00:01:27,459 --> 00:01:28,688
Who would hit us?

25
00:01:28,689 --> 00:01:30,799
We're here to eat fried chicken.

26
00:01:31,099 --> 00:01:34,870
Auntie said she made octopus-shaped sausages for us.

27
00:01:36,030 --> 00:01:38,599
It's okay. You can be honest with me, okay?

28
00:01:39,099 --> 00:01:40,339
I'm here, so you're safe now.

29
00:01:40,340 --> 00:01:42,540
Are they being mean to you?

30
00:01:42,709 --> 00:01:43,839
Let me see.

31
00:01:43,840 --> 00:01:45,439
Why would they be mean to us?

32
00:01:47,379 --> 00:01:48,879
No, they're not mean to us.

33
00:01:49,010 --> 00:01:52,079
What? Then why did you call me so many times?

34
00:01:53,519 --> 00:01:55,420
Why did you keep calling me?

35
00:01:57,790 --> 00:01:59,260
Because I missed you.

36
00:02:00,930 --> 00:02:03,599
Me too. I missed you.

37
00:02:04,400 --> 00:02:07,170
That's why I called you.

38
00:02:08,030 --> 00:02:11,139
Can we only call you when something bad happens?

39
00:02:12,900 --> 00:02:14,539
(Dahee Fried Chicken)

40
00:02:22,280 --> 00:02:23,780
Gyeo Rye, where are you going?

41
00:02:24,219 --> 00:02:26,050
Have some fried chicken with us!

42
00:02:26,319 --> 00:02:27,490
(Dahee Fried Chicken)

43
00:02:41,469 --> 00:02:42,469
Hey.

44
00:02:45,939 --> 00:02:47,009
Take this.

45
00:02:48,210 --> 00:02:50,280
I can fry up some more for the kids.

46
00:02:59,349 --> 00:03:00,789
I may not be the best auntie,

47
00:03:02,349 --> 00:03:03,590
but we didn't hit them.

48
00:03:04,719 --> 00:03:06,620
Even the money from my great-aunt's life insurance.

49
00:03:06,689 --> 00:03:09,229
I deposited the whole sum into a bank account in the kids' names.

50
00:03:11,400 --> 00:03:13,128
We used to live in a studio apartment,

51
00:03:13,129 --> 00:03:14,870
and it was too small for the four of us.

52
00:03:16,030 --> 00:03:17,969
So at the moment, we're staying at my great-aunt's place.

53
00:03:18,539 --> 00:03:19,900
We won't steal the house from them.

54
00:03:20,810 --> 00:03:24,280
If they want us to leave, we can move out at any time.

55
00:03:25,110 --> 00:03:27,310
You can keep checking.

56
00:03:29,650 --> 00:03:30,650
I'm sorry.

57
00:03:34,719 --> 00:03:35,719
I'm really sorry.

58
00:03:36,419 --> 00:03:37,460
Don't be.

59
00:03:39,020 --> 00:03:40,289
Thank you...

60
00:03:41,460 --> 00:03:42,889
for looking out for them.

61
00:03:45,860 --> 00:03:47,469
You see, I could've been mean to them.

62
00:03:48,530 --> 00:03:50,229
But then, you'd come after me.

63
00:03:51,539 --> 00:03:53,199
I kept being reminded of your threats.

64
00:03:56,210 --> 00:03:57,479
I didn't do anything bad to them.

65
00:03:58,210 --> 00:03:59,710
You did the right thing.

66
00:04:01,080 --> 00:04:02,750
If it weren't for you,

67
00:04:03,180 --> 00:04:05,150
I wouldn't be as attentive to them.

68
00:04:07,620 --> 00:04:08,719
What you did was right.

69
00:04:16,259 --> 00:04:17,759
Keep watching out for them.

70
00:04:18,930 --> 00:04:21,670
For other kids too.

71
00:04:23,470 --> 00:04:24,540
Bye.

72
00:04:41,819 --> 00:04:44,989
Gyeo Rye! We can call you when we miss you, right?

73
00:04:44,990 --> 00:04:46,420
We can call you, right?

74
00:04:49,329 --> 00:04:50,660
Yes, feel free to call me.

75
00:04:50,959 --> 00:04:52,000
- Okay! - Okay!

76
00:04:56,529 --> 00:04:58,370
- Let's go inside. - Okay.

77
00:05:28,600 --> 00:05:30,569
(Chicken)

78
00:05:36,569 --> 00:05:37,680
You haven't eaten yet?

79
00:05:38,910 --> 00:05:39,910
Should I make you something?

80
00:05:51,560 --> 00:05:53,360
How did I turn out like this?

81
00:06:39,540 --> 00:06:41,438
(Death doesn't end everything.)

82
00:06:41,439 --> 00:06:44,680
"Death doesn't end everything."

83
00:06:45,579 --> 00:06:46,639
Perhaps...

84
00:06:48,980 --> 00:06:51,120
when I first met them,

85
00:06:53,350 --> 00:06:55,949
I assumed they'd be bad people...

86
00:06:57,220 --> 00:06:58,459
and kept believing it...

87
00:06:59,589 --> 00:07:01,660
because I was so afraid that the kids would end up like me.

88
00:07:05,259 --> 00:07:06,259
No.

89
00:07:09,230 --> 00:07:10,300
Just like...

90
00:07:14,009 --> 00:07:16,469
the young Yoon Gyeo Rye who was always alone...

91
00:07:16,470 --> 00:07:18,379
needed Superman,

92
00:07:20,079 --> 00:07:22,579
you just wanted to help them and keep them safe.

93
00:07:26,449 --> 00:07:29,589
I really want to leave my past behind and move on already.

94
00:07:30,050 --> 00:07:33,360
Gosh, I'm so sick of getting dragged back to my past.

95
00:07:36,730 --> 00:07:38,959
Can I keep living like this?

96
00:07:42,230 --> 00:07:44,600
Like I said to you a while back...

97
00:07:46,870 --> 00:07:48,810
Life goes on, so just keep on living.

98
00:07:51,180 --> 00:07:52,639
You're doing well.

99
00:07:53,680 --> 00:07:56,610
You still don't seem to know that you're such a wonderful person.

100
00:07:57,750 --> 00:07:59,350
- Me? - Yes.

101
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:01,949
So many people like you.

102
00:08:03,050 --> 00:08:04,060
Who?

103
00:08:06,220 --> 00:08:07,230
Team Genie.

104
00:08:08,389 --> 00:08:09,860
Jae Yeon, Ho Yeon.

105
00:08:10,660 --> 00:08:11,959
And everyone at the hospital.

106
00:08:13,870 --> 00:08:15,029
And you, Seo Yeon Joo.

107
00:08:15,800 --> 00:08:16,800
Yes.

108
00:08:17,839 --> 00:08:19,100
I like you the most.

109
00:09:10,389 --> 00:09:15,389
(If You Wish Upon Me)

110
00:09:16,330 --> 00:09:18,960
I want to let it happen naturally.

111
00:09:19,230 --> 00:09:20,629
Where is she?

112
00:09:22,500 --> 00:09:23,730
I need to sound natural too.

113
00:09:26,639 --> 00:09:28,839
You must be swamped with work.

114
00:09:28,840 --> 00:09:30,309
Take a quick break and drink this.

115
00:09:31,240 --> 00:09:33,879
Perfect. I almost sound like a Seoul native.

116
00:09:35,909 --> 00:09:38,519
What? My goodness. Sir.

117
00:09:39,149 --> 00:09:41,149
Sir? Are you all right?

118
00:09:41,389 --> 00:09:43,389
Sir. Are you okay?

119
00:09:43,820 --> 00:09:47,289
Oh, no. I'll go get a doctor for you.

120
00:09:47,759 --> 00:09:50,159
It's okay. I tripped and fell. That's all.

121
00:09:51,059 --> 00:09:54,099
Would you take me back to my room?

122
00:09:54,100 --> 00:09:56,970
Oh, don't. Try not to move so suddenly.

123
00:10:02,539 --> 00:10:05,379
By the way, when were you admitted?

124
00:10:05,610 --> 00:10:06,808
I haven't seen you before.

125
00:10:06,809 --> 00:10:07,879
Oh, right.

126
00:10:08,580 --> 00:10:10,408
Less than a week ago.

127
00:10:10,409 --> 00:10:11,480
I see.

128
00:10:12,679 --> 00:10:15,620
So it's only been a few days.

129
00:10:45,620 --> 00:10:46,720
You're here.

130
00:11:00,399 --> 00:11:03,070
It must've been heavy. Why did you bring so many things?

131
00:11:03,700 --> 00:11:06,269
She only likes the side dishes that I make, you know.

132
00:11:06,440 --> 00:11:08,809
She probably has no appetite right now.

133
00:11:09,009 --> 00:11:10,070
Right.

134
00:11:11,440 --> 00:11:13,679
She really hasn't been eating much.

135
00:11:16,009 --> 00:11:18,279
You know, the person who did that to her hair.

136
00:11:19,580 --> 00:11:21,250
I think it was Yoon Ki Chun.

137
00:11:22,419 --> 00:11:24,190
He denied it,

138
00:11:24,389 --> 00:11:26,019
but it's obvious.

139
00:11:29,129 --> 00:11:31,860
Maybe we shouldn't have done what we did.

140
00:11:33,000 --> 00:11:35,169
Not because of that jerk.

141
00:11:35,230 --> 00:11:37,799
But I'm worried about Mr. Kang and Nurse Seo.

142
00:11:37,970 --> 00:11:40,370
We're old anyway, so it's fine.

143
00:11:40,769 --> 00:11:43,109
What if something happens to Nurse Seo?

144
00:11:43,110 --> 00:11:45,110
I'm so worried.

145
00:11:46,879 --> 00:11:49,179
- I'm worried too. - Anything could happen,

146
00:11:50,179 --> 00:11:53,178
the two of you should hunker down at home for the time being.

147
00:11:53,179 --> 00:11:56,049
You should be careful too.

148
00:12:02,429 --> 00:12:05,600
Up until just a few days ago, we were so happy together.

149
00:12:07,000 --> 00:12:09,970
It all feels like a dream.

150
00:12:12,500 --> 00:12:16,110
Just like how life flies by before you even know it.

151
00:12:16,639 --> 00:12:21,710
Deep in the valley

152
00:12:23,679 --> 00:12:27,648
Deep in the valley

153
00:12:27,649 --> 00:12:32,320
There is a sunny spot

154
00:12:33,659 --> 00:12:35,929
Withstanding the rain and wind

155
00:12:37,600 --> 00:12:40,799
For many years

156
00:12:42,200 --> 00:12:45,840
Is a nameless

157
00:12:48,570 --> 00:12:52,809
A nameless

158
00:12:56,049 --> 00:13:00,779
Wooden mound marker

159
00:13:02,049 --> 00:13:08,789
My faraway hometown

160
00:13:09,190 --> 00:13:13,559
My friend

161
00:13:15,700 --> 00:13:17,700
The skies

162
00:13:22,870 --> 00:13:25,279
I left behind

163
00:13:28,610 --> 00:13:30,980
I miss it

164
00:13:34,750 --> 00:13:35,919
Oh, boy.

165
00:13:37,490 --> 00:13:38,559
Hello.

166
00:13:40,659 --> 00:13:41,759
Have you eaten...

167
00:13:46,429 --> 00:13:47,429
Hello.

168
00:14:04,620 --> 00:14:05,649
Hello...

169
00:14:11,419 --> 00:14:12,460
What's going on?

170
00:14:22,000 --> 00:14:23,169
Hey, Gyeo Rye.

171
00:14:24,070 --> 00:14:25,700
Where have you been?

172
00:14:28,669 --> 00:14:30,070
What is going on?

173
00:14:33,210 --> 00:14:35,250
Why is everyone avoiding me?

174
00:14:36,379 --> 00:14:37,950
What happened?

175
00:14:38,720 --> 00:14:39,750
Gyeo Rye.

176
00:14:43,220 --> 00:14:45,320
What? Mr. Gu?

177
00:14:46,320 --> 00:14:49,830
Yes. He was found like that this morning.

178
00:14:50,429 --> 00:14:53,099
- My gosh. - What happened?

179
00:14:53,100 --> 00:14:55,429
- Who did this? - Who hurt him?

180
00:14:56,330 --> 00:14:59,168
There is someone I'm suspecting.

181
00:14:59,169 --> 00:15:00,970
Okay, please tell me more.

182
00:15:02,340 --> 00:15:04,779
- From what I've heard... - Yes.

183
00:15:05,440 --> 00:15:07,649
He's being treated at a hospital nearby,

184
00:15:08,149 --> 00:15:10,149
but he hasn't regained consciousness yet.

185
00:15:10,309 --> 00:15:13,750
Only the cameras in that part of the building were broken.

186
00:15:14,419 --> 00:15:18,419
The police said it had to be someone who knew the building's layout well.

187
00:15:18,759 --> 00:15:22,490
But we couldn't reach you because you don't have a cell phone.

188
00:15:22,759 --> 00:15:24,959
And you weren't at the hospital until this morning.

189
00:15:24,960 --> 00:15:26,259
What? So are you saying I...

190
00:15:28,070 --> 00:15:29,699
I got a cell phone.

191
00:15:29,700 --> 00:15:33,139
And I had to step out to meet someone.

192
00:15:33,470 --> 00:15:35,309
You see, rumours...

193
00:15:35,970 --> 00:15:38,878
could save or kill you.

194
00:15:38,879 --> 00:15:40,409
Rumours? What rumours?

195
00:15:41,610 --> 00:15:45,580
In the past, you killed people...

196
00:15:46,980 --> 00:15:49,720
I mean, before you went to jail,

197
00:15:50,549 --> 00:15:52,519
you hurt people...

198
00:15:52,759 --> 00:15:55,090
and did bad things.

199
00:15:55,259 --> 00:15:57,089
Rumour has it that you came here...

200
00:15:57,090 --> 00:16:00,600
to do community service because you had an ulterior motive.

201
00:16:03,370 --> 00:16:04,570
Ulterior motive? Like what?

202
00:16:06,740 --> 00:16:09,570
To steal the morphine in the safe.

203
00:16:16,110 --> 00:16:17,149
Gosh.

204
00:16:17,919 --> 00:16:20,649
Who is spreading such rumours?

205
00:16:21,620 --> 00:16:23,620
We have no idea how the rumours began.

206
00:16:24,490 --> 00:16:26,820
That's what it's like with most rumours.

207
00:16:29,629 --> 00:16:31,159
All I heard was that...

208
00:16:32,159 --> 00:16:36,299
someone who had known you for a long time visited the hospital.

209
00:16:37,600 --> 00:16:40,440
- You know Yoon Gyeo Rye, right? - Yes.

210
00:16:44,340 --> 00:16:46,740
Rumour has it that he came to this hospital...

211
00:16:46,840 --> 00:16:48,579
to get morphine.

212
00:16:48,580 --> 00:16:51,949
I heard Yoon Gyeo Rye came here to steal morphine.

213
00:16:51,950 --> 00:16:56,289
I suppose that person wanted to deliberately get you into trouble.

214
00:16:56,919 --> 00:16:59,889
Who would do such a thing? And why?

215
00:17:22,849 --> 00:17:23,910
Gyeo Rye.

216
00:17:24,380 --> 00:17:25,819
Did you hear about Mr. Gu?

217
00:17:26,849 --> 00:17:27,890
Gyeo Rye!

218
00:17:54,039 --> 00:17:55,349
What are you doing here?

219
00:17:56,250 --> 00:17:58,349
Are you afraid that I'd call the cops on you?

220
00:17:58,450 --> 00:18:00,180
I will pay for what I did.

221
00:18:06,160 --> 00:18:07,220
You see,

222
00:18:08,859 --> 00:18:10,390
I can call the cops on you too.

223
00:18:13,799 --> 00:18:15,069
So...

224
00:18:15,930 --> 00:18:17,700
you'd better stop now and leave quietly.

225
00:18:19,069 --> 00:18:20,069
Okay?

226
00:18:21,539 --> 00:18:24,910
He did nothing wrong. Why are you messing with him?

227
00:18:25,680 --> 00:18:28,210
You know he has nothing to do with Mr. Kang!

228
00:18:31,109 --> 00:18:32,180
If you...

229
00:18:34,220 --> 00:18:36,589
care about your son even just a little bit,

230
00:18:37,750 --> 00:18:39,589
stop this and leave.

231
00:18:40,220 --> 00:18:42,390
Please leave, okay?

232
00:18:44,859 --> 00:18:46,160
Gyeo Rye...

233
00:18:47,599 --> 00:18:50,269
He's been through so much.

234
00:18:50,970 --> 00:18:55,109
I suppose you really like my son.

235
00:19:01,349 --> 00:19:04,950
My son, Yoon Gyeo Rye.

236
00:19:05,650 --> 00:19:09,549
It looks like you love him very much.

237
00:19:10,819 --> 00:19:11,859
Yes.

238
00:19:13,059 --> 00:19:14,119
That's right.

239
00:19:15,490 --> 00:19:16,660
I love him.

240
00:19:17,690 --> 00:19:20,329
- So... - My goodness.

241
00:19:21,299 --> 00:19:22,599
Why do you think Kang Tae Sik...

242
00:19:23,230 --> 00:19:26,299
brought my son here?

243
00:19:27,970 --> 00:19:29,670
Had he never brought him here,

244
00:19:29,910 --> 00:19:33,240
he wouldn't have had to see me again or deal with this.

245
00:19:33,640 --> 00:19:34,750
My son, Yoon Gyeo Rye.

246
00:19:37,079 --> 00:19:40,420
And think about it.

247
00:19:41,690 --> 00:19:43,890
I didn't look for Gyeo Rye.

248
00:19:44,789 --> 00:19:47,319
Kang Tae Sik brought him here.

249
00:19:48,890 --> 00:19:51,358
Kang Tae Sik nearly killed me,

250
00:19:51,359 --> 00:19:52,799
then I met my son.

251
00:19:53,529 --> 00:19:57,000
All of this is Kang Tae Sik's fault.

252
00:19:59,970 --> 00:20:03,209
My gosh. Are you going to keep this up until the end?

253
00:20:03,210 --> 00:20:04,839
The end?

254
00:20:05,680 --> 00:20:07,339
We're only getting started.

255
00:20:11,980 --> 00:20:13,779
Kang Tae Sik!

256
00:20:14,450 --> 00:20:16,889
You used to sell pork soup for a living.

257
00:20:16,890 --> 00:20:19,220
Thanks to me, you got the CEO title.

258
00:20:19,589 --> 00:20:23,190
How dare you deceive me like this?

259
00:20:54,359 --> 00:20:55,789
(Incoming Call: 010-4465-890)

260
00:21:02,269 --> 00:21:03,869
Hello? Who is it?

261
00:21:05,940 --> 00:21:07,000
It's me.

262
00:21:08,069 --> 00:21:09,140
Hey, Gyeo Rye.

263
00:21:10,369 --> 00:21:11,440
How are you feeling?

264
00:21:12,480 --> 00:21:13,509
Are you okay?

265
00:21:14,680 --> 00:21:16,048
Yes, I am.

266
00:21:16,049 --> 00:21:18,579
I constantly eat, sleep, eat, and sleep.

267
00:21:19,450 --> 00:21:20,450
It's comfortable here.

268
00:21:22,490 --> 00:21:25,359
I see. That's a relief.

269
00:21:25,960 --> 00:21:29,859
But you don't sound okay to me.

270
00:21:30,089 --> 00:21:31,190
Did something happen?

271
00:21:31,630 --> 00:21:32,660
No, not really.

272
00:21:35,029 --> 00:21:36,500
Nothing big.

273
00:21:37,269 --> 00:21:38,269
Then what is it?

274
00:21:39,799 --> 00:21:40,799
You know...

275
00:21:44,609 --> 00:21:48,079
